Cops in Limpopo have
offered a reward of up to R250 000 for valuable information. In order for the funds
to be released the information should lead to the arrest and conviction of the
suspects responsible for the killing of two councilors of the Mogalakwena
Municipality. Valtyn Kekana, who was
54 at the time and Ralph Kanyane 32, were gunned down by an unknown attacker on
23 July 2019. The councilors were
apparently seated in a vehicle when the gunman approached and started firing
shots at them. They both died at the
scene. The assailant
allegedly fled from the scene on foot after the incident. Police spokesperson
Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo appealled to anyone with valuable information that
can assist the police in arresting the suspect to come forward. â€œAnyone who can be
able to recognize the person running in the footage or picture below, to
contact Lieutenant Colonel Richard Boshomane at 0798945501 or call the toll
free number 08600 10111. Mojapelo said callers
may choose to remain anonymous and confidentiality for any information received
will be guaranteed.